        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/2/234/1",
        "text": [
          ": مَنْ أَدْمَنَ قِرَاءَهَ لا أُقْسِمُ وَ کَانَ یَعْمَلُ بِهَا بَعَثَهُ اللَّهُ عَزَّ وَ جَلَّ مَعَ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ص مِنْ قَبْرِهِ فِی أَحْسَنِ صُورَهٍ وَ یُبَشِّرُهُ وَ یَضْحَکُ فِی وَجْهِهِ حَتَّی یَجُوزَ عَلَی الصِّرَاطِ وَ الْمِیزَانِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
            "1. From the previous chain from al-Hassan from al-Hussain b. Abi al-’Ala from Abi Basir from Abi Ja’far (a.s.) who said: Whoever recites Surah Qiyamat regularly and acts upon it, Allah would raise him from the grave with the Messenger of Allah (s.a.w.s.) in the best form. He would be given glad-tiding and he would pass through Sirat and Mizan smiling."
          ]
        }
      }
